<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Amphenol (APH)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Amphenol Corporation. Using actual FY2025 financials, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })} · Data: FY2025 10-K</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  {roundedIV !== null ? (
    <>
      <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
      <div class="verdict-card">
        <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
        <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
        <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice?.toFixed(2) || 'N/A'} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
        <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
          {verdictText}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
      <div class="stats-row">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${(fyRevenue / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
          <div class="stat-label">FY2025 Revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${(fcf2025 / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${fyEps?.toFixed(2)}</div>
          <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">{fyOpMargin !== null ? (fyOpMargin * 100).toFixed(1) + '%' : 'N/A'}</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
      <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
      <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model. No multiples, no comparables. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">1</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
          <p>Amphenol generated <strong>${(fcf2025 / 1000).toFixed(2)} billion</strong> in free cash flow in FY2025. This is the operating cash flow minus capital expenditures — the real cash the business produces.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">2</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
          <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This aligns with Amphenol's strong historical execution and continued demand in electronics and communications, balanced with a realistic outlook for mature scaling.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">3</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
          <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}% forever</strong>. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>: Terminal Value = FCF₆ ÷ (discount rate − terminal growth rate). This represents the value of the company into perpetuity.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">4</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
          <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}%</strong>. This required rate of return adequately compensates for equity risk above the 10Y Treasury (4.18%).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">5</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
          <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({(sharesOutstanding / 1000).toFixed(2)}B) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
      <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>

      <div class="assumption-grid">
        <div class="assumption-card">
          <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
          <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
          <div class="rationale">
            A 10% growth rate appropriately factors in Amphenol's consistent M&A-driven compounding and strong end-market demand, while maintaining a slight margin of safety against cyclical slowdowns.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="assumption-card">
          <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
          <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
          <div class="rationale">
            10Y Treasury: 4.18%. We use 10% as a standard institutional hurdle rate, reflecting the required return for a large-cap, reliable compounder in the technology components space.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="assumption-card">
          <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
          <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
          <div class="rationale">
